              <div class="content__page-desc">
                <h3>Gas Ovens</h3>
                <p>
                  Gas ovens are favored for their precise temperature control and quick heating capabilities. However, they come with specific repair needs primarily related to their gas components. Common issues include problems with the igniter, which may fail to spark and ignite the gas, or a malfunctioning gas valve that could disrupt the flow of gas to the oven. Thermostat issues can also arise, leading to inaccurate temperature readings. Safety concerns are paramount with gas ovens, so issues like gas leaks must be addressed immediately by a professional. Regular inspections and maintenance, such as checking and cleaning the burners and ensuring proper gas line connections, can help prevent these problems and ensure safe operation.
                </p>
              </div>

              <div class="content__page-desc">
                <h3>Electric Ovens</h3>
                <p>
                  Electric ovens are known for their even heating and reliability, but they can encounter several repair needs mainly related to their electrical components. Common problems include malfunctioning heating elements, which may stop producing heat, and faulty thermostats that can result in incorrect temperature settings. Control board failures are also a frequent issue, particularly in more advanced models with digital interfaces. These problems often require professional diagnosis and replacement of the faulty parts. Regular maintenance, such as cleaning the interior and inspecting the electrical connections, can help mitigate these issues and extend the oven's lifespan.
                </p>
              </div>

              <div class="content__page-desc">
                <h3>Convection Ovens</h3>
                <p>
                  Convection ovens use a fan to circulate hot air, providing faster and more even cooking. However, this added complexity introduces unique repair needs. Common issues include malfunctioning fans or motors, which can lead to uneven cooking or complete fan failure. Heating elements and control boards can also experience problems similar to those in standard electric ovens. Regular maintenance is crucial for convection ovens, including cleaning the fan and motor assembly and ensuring the air circulation system is functioning correctly. Addressing these issues promptly can help maintain the oven's efficiency and cooking performance.
                </p>
              </div>

