                <h3>Temperature Inaccuracy</h3>
                <p>
                  One of the most common issues with ovens is temperature inaccuracy, where the oven does not heat to the temperature set on the dial. This can be caused by a faulty thermostat, a malfunctioning temperature sensor, or worn-out heating elements. As a result, food may cook unevenly, take longer to prepare, or burn on the outside while remaining undercooked inside. Regular calibration and maintenance checks can help identify and resolve these issues. In some cases, replacing the thermostat or sensor may be necessary to restore accurate temperature control.
                </p>
